OL,3,C'It's a nightmare': Grieving father
OL,4,Cshocked by increasing 'cost of dying'
OL,6,FThey found that basic funeral fees -
OL,7,Fsuch as the provision of a hearse and
OL,8,Fcaring for the deceased - had
OL,9,Fincreased by approximately 15% between
OL,10,F2022 and May 2024.
OL,12,FAndy Errington-Rennell, a Funeral
OL,13,FDirector at Pitcher and Le Quesne,
OL,14,Fsays they are not immune to increasing
OL,15,Foperating costs.
OL,17,FHe explains: "We do everything as a
OL,18,Fbusiness to keep costs down. Sometimes
OL,19,Fit means that some of our fees which
OL,20,Fshould in theory go up, don't go up.
